{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, offset spatula, scissors, oven","id":"r125870","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-wFpLfk5bdoM\/XZap37uYkyI\/AAAAAAAAhWA\/Ie7lZyVL2K0IJ_9ie2EdqaV21LiW15enACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Du3Pw7lPcE-j8Wx_.png","title":"Pear leathers","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","ingredients2":[{"content":"3 ripe pears, peeled, cored and cut into cubes (3 cm) (approx. 500 g pear flesh)"},{"content":"2 tsp lemon juice"},{"content":"&frac18; tsp ground cinnamon (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"0.2 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"6.2 g","calories":"154 kJ \/ 36 kcal"},"preparations2":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 50°C. Line 2 large baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place pears and lemon juice into mixing bowl and cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Add cinnamon (optional) and blend <b>30 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then cook <b>20 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>."},{"content":"Transfer mixture onto prepared baking trays. Using an offset spatula, spread mixture evenly across baking paper (2-3 mm thickness). Mixture will thin out during baking. Bake for 6-8 hours (50°C) or until pureé is dry to the touch and pliable (see Tips). Trim ends and, using scissors, cut dried pear mixture into 8 strips (8 cm length), then roll up to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Cooking times will vary depending on your oven and the thickness of your pureé. If after 5 hours of baking, your pureé is still quite wet to touch, increase your oven temperature to 60°C and continue drying until dry to the touch.","These pear leathers are delicious served with a little blue cheese or as part of a cheese platter."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","8h 25m","8 portions"]}